snippet.textDisplay: From an art historical standpoint, there are so many intentional elements in these works of visual art. As I've written before, the choice to show the umpire checking the hands and glove of the pitcher is intentional; it's not really part of the highlights, but it is Major League Baseball's way of publicizing that they are regularly enforcing this rule. Showing the batters greeting the catcher and umpire in their first AB shows the kind of culture MLB embodies. And they'll sprinkle in shots of kids with their parents in the seats to show the family-friendly product they offer.
